1
00:00:25,989 --> 00:00:30,989
[ominous music]

2
00:00:38,168 --> 00:00:43,168
[ Indistinct whispers ]

3
00:00:47,094 --> 00:00:49,679
TERRY: Neal?

4
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:52,848
Neal, come on, wake up.

5
00:00:52,849 --> 00:00:54,392
Hey, come on, kid, get up.

6
00:00:54,393 --> 00:00:55,601
We're almost home.

7
00:00:55,602 --> 00:01:00,602
[ <i>Gasps</i> ]

8
00:01:11,910 --> 00:01:14,954
How long was I out?

9
00:01:14,955 --> 00:01:16,372
All the way from the airport,

10
00:01:16,373 --> 00:01:20,626
about three hours.

11
00:01:20,627 --> 00:01:25,627
What, didn't you sleep
last night?

12
00:01:25,924 --> 00:01:28,634
Looks about the same around here.

13
00:01:28,635 --> 00:01:30,344
Yeah,yeah.

14
00:01:30,345 --> 00:01:32,555
<i>The, um...</i>

15
00:01:32,556 --> 00:01:35,975
snow just all came off last week.

16
00:01:35,976 --> 00:01:38,436
It was real nice.
You would've...

17
00:01:38,437 --> 00:01:40,479
You would've liked it.

18
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:43,441
Yeah.

19
00:01:43,442 --> 00:01:48,442
Too bad I had to miss it then.

20
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:55,244
So I guess it's a lot, <i>uh...</i>

21
00:01:55,245 --> 00:01:58,748
a lot warmer in Florida, huh?

22
00:01:58,749 --> 00:02:03,749
Depends on
what you mean by warm.

23
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:07,590
See you still got
that mumbling thing.

24
00:02:07,591 --> 00:02:09,925
I don't know.

25
00:02:09,926 --> 00:02:14,926
You see, Aunt Sara
didn't seem to care if I talked or not.

26
00:02:18,477 --> 00:02:21,520
Actually, Sara cared a lot.

27
00:02:21,521 --> 00:02:23,272
Could've fooled me.

28
00:02:23,273 --> 00:02:25,858
Really?
[ laughs ] Really

29
00:02:25,859 --> 00:02:28,444
You know, kid,
when someone takes your ass in

30
00:02:28,445 --> 00:02:31,072
and doesn't kick it out
after two years,

31
00:02:31,073 --> 00:02:34,366
that's 'cause
they actually give a shit.

32
00:02:34,367 --> 00:02:37,453
And she didn't want you gone,

33
00:02:37,454 --> 00:02:40,289
if that's what you think,
either, okay?

34
00:02:40,290 --> 00:02:45,290
It's 'cause the new lady
wants to meet me, right?

35
00:02:48,465 --> 00:02:51,092
So you did read
the letters I sent you then.

36
00:02:51,093 --> 00:02:56,093
Yeah.

37
00:02:56,723 --> 00:03:00,726
Well, I didn't know one way
or the other, you know.

38
00:03:00,727 --> 00:03:03,771
Response would have been nice.

39
00:03:03,772 --> 00:03:08,772
I had some,
but they weren't very nice.

40
00:03:14,074 --> 00:03:17,827
What does Paulie think of her?

41
00:03:17,828 --> 00:03:20,955
Paulie thinks the world of her.

42
00:03:20,956 --> 00:03:24,792
Which is one of the reasons
why I decided

43
00:03:24,793 --> 00:03:27,545
to move forward with her.

44
00:03:27,546 --> 00:03:32,546
And one of the big reasons
why she wants to get to know you.

45
00:03:34,094 --> 00:03:39,094
How is Paulie?

46
00:03:43,395 --> 00:03:45,479
He's fine.

47
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:50,480
He's good.

48
00:04:07,627 --> 00:04:10,212
[ People conversing ]

49
00:04:10,213 --> 00:04:12,798
- TERRY: [whispers ] Aw, shit.
- NEAL: Dad?

50
00:04:12,799 --> 00:04:16,302
I'm sorry. Come on.

51
00:04:16,303 --> 00:04:21,303
It's gonna be all right.
Come on.

52
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:26,812
- [guests clapping ]
- TERRY: Hey.

53
00:04:26,813 --> 00:04:29,732
It was Angela's idea.

54
00:04:29,733 --> 00:04:31,025
I'm gonna love her.

55
00:04:31,026 --> 00:04:32,818
Hey, come on, this is important
to her, all right?

56
00:04:32,819 --> 00:04:34,195
So just try and remember
what a smile is

57
00:04:34,196 --> 00:04:36,530
and slap it on your face
for a few minutes, please?

58
00:04:36,531 --> 00:04:38,365
ANGELA: [gasps] Ohh!

59
00:04:38,366 --> 00:04:40,242
[laughs]

60
00:04:40,243 --> 00:04:42,661
Oh, my! Oh, my!

61
00:04:42,662 --> 00:04:46,415
Oh, so nice
to finally meet you, honey!

62
00:04:46,416 --> 00:04:47,791
TERRY:
This is Angela, obviously.

63
00:04:47,792 --> 00:04:49,543
ANGELA: Oh, welcome home.

64
00:04:49,544 --> 00:04:50,794
I'm Angela.

65
00:04:50,795 --> 00:04:52,880
Oh, so nice to see you.

66
00:04:52,881 --> 00:04:54,340
You know,
you must be very hungry.

67
00:04:54,341 --> 00:04:56,383
You want something to eat,
something to drink?

68
00:04:56,384 --> 00:04:58,427
I mean, I've made plenty <i>of...</i>

69
00:04:58,428 --> 00:05:03,428
[voice becomes distorted ]

70
00:05:15,403 --> 00:05:17,905
...in person.
You really are a cutie!

71
00:05:17,906 --> 00:05:19,823
- Oh!
- Where's Paulie?

72
00:05:19,824 --> 00:05:21,617
Yeah, where is
your youngest, Hausman?

73
00:05:21,618 --> 00:05:23,535
I figured he'd be out here
dancing for joy to have Neal back.

74
00:05:23,536 --> 00:05:25,579
TERRY: Oh. Uh, well,
you know, Paul's, <i>uh...</i>

75
00:05:25,580 --> 00:05:26,997
Taking a nap, actually.

76
00:05:26,998 --> 00:05:28,582
Yeah, he's had a little fever recently,

77
00:05:28,583 --> 00:05:30,292
and he's just getting over it.

78
00:05:30,293 --> 00:05:33,003
TERRY: You know, we just want
to keep him rested for school tomorrow.

79
00:05:33,004 --> 00:05:36,090
Hey, Neal, you remember me, right?

80
00:05:36,091 --> 00:05:37,758
Mr. Evans.

81
00:05:37,759 --> 00:05:39,551
Hey, kept an eye on your dad

82
00:05:39,552 --> 00:05:41,011
while you were staying
at your aunt's.

83
00:05:41,012 --> 00:05:42,554
Made sure he didn't
get into any trouble.

84
00:05:42,555 --> 00:05:44,223
Are you sure about that?

85
00:05:44,224 --> 00:05:46,642
I think he snuck in a new wife
when you weren't looking.

86
00:05:46,643 --> 00:05:47,851
[laughs]

87
00:05:47,852 --> 00:05:52,852
Yeah, anyway, you remember my boys,
Richard and Roger?

88
00:05:54,401 --> 00:05:56,318
Hey, guys.

89
00:05:56,319 --> 00:05:57,695
They've been talking
nonstop about you

90
00:05:57,696 --> 00:05:59,655
ever since they heard
you were coming back.

91
00:05:59,656 --> 00:06:02,491
Hey, we would love to have you over
for our own little welcome back.

92
00:06:02,492 --> 00:06:04,201
You know, you and your brother
can come over for dinner,

93
00:06:04,202 --> 00:06:05,452
you can stay the night,
we'll hang out.

94
00:06:05,453 --> 00:06:08,455
- It'll be great.
- Thanks.

95
00:06:08,456 --> 00:06:09,748
I'm gonna go tell Paulie.

96
00:06:09,749 --> 00:06:11,041
MR. EVANS:
All right, great.

97
00:06:11,042 --> 00:06:12,334
Great to see you...

98
00:06:12,335 --> 00:06:17,335
Neal.

99
00:06:23,346 --> 00:06:28,346
CARA: Neal?

100
00:06:29,602 --> 00:06:33,564
Hey, Cara.

101
00:06:33,565 --> 00:06:36,650
I'm sorry I left
without saying good-bye.

102
00:06:36,651 --> 00:06:37,943
We just left, like, overnight.

103
00:06:37,944 --> 00:06:40,070
It's okay.

104
00:06:40,071 --> 00:06:42,781
I'm sorry I never got
the chance to say sorry

105
00:06:42,782 --> 00:06:47,119
about, you know, what happened.

106
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,871
Thanks.

107
00:06:48,872 --> 00:06:51,081
Hey, Cara?

108
00:06:51,082 --> 00:06:52,583
Gonna marry that nut job?

109
00:06:52,584 --> 00:06:55,294
You better keep him
away from matches.

110
00:06:55,295 --> 00:06:59,340
Shut up!

111
00:06:59,341 --> 00:07:04,341
I'm sorry.
My brothers are idiots.

112
00:07:04,637 --> 00:07:05,888
It's okay.

113
00:07:05,889 --> 00:07:08,766
My brother's inside,
so I should go.

114
00:07:08,767 --> 00:07:11,393
Cool.

115
00:07:11,394 --> 00:07:16,394
It's good seeing you, Neal.

116
00:07:30,163 --> 00:07:35,163
It's gorgeous.

117
00:08:09,452 --> 00:08:14,452
[thud]

118
00:08:17,460 --> 00:08:22,460
[ Rapid breathing ]

119
00:09:21,065 --> 00:09:26,065
Paulie?

120
00:09:27,739 --> 00:09:32,739
Paulie?

121
00:09:34,787 --> 00:09:39,787
Paulie!

122
00:09:42,462 --> 00:09:47,462
Paulie!

123
00:09:52,222 --> 00:09:57,222
Paulie?

124
00:10:05,151 --> 00:10:10,151
[thud echoing ]

125
00:10:40,228 --> 00:10:41,228
[thud]

126
00:10:41,229 --> 00:10:46,229
[panting]

127
00:11:08,339 --> 00:11:13,339
[creaking ]

128
00:11:40,413 --> 00:11:42,247
Paulie, Jesus Christ!

129
00:11:42,248 --> 00:11:45,125
You really scared me, buddy.

130
00:11:45,126 --> 00:11:46,376
You're not Neal.

131
00:11:46,377 --> 00:11:48,170
No, of course, I am.

132
00:11:48,171 --> 00:11:50,297
It's really me, Paulie.

133
00:11:50,298 --> 00:11:51,506
Prove it.

134
00:11:51,507 --> 00:11:54,301
Okay.

135
00:11:54,302 --> 00:11:55,677
Well, Dad, probably flipped out

136
00:11:55,678 --> 00:12:00,678
when he found out
about these, right?

137
00:12:10,860 --> 00:12:13,236
It pretended to be you
so many times.

138
00:12:13,237 --> 00:12:16,365
Paulie, don't talk like that.

139
00:12:16,366 --> 00:12:21,366
TERRY: Hey, what the hell's
going on in here?

140
00:12:22,455 --> 00:12:26,875
God damn it!

141
00:12:26,876 --> 00:12:29,211
Paulie, what the hell
you doing up here?

142
00:12:29,212 --> 00:12:30,212
How many times
do I have to tell you

143
00:12:30,213 --> 00:12:31,338
not to go through these boxes?

144
00:12:31,339 --> 00:12:32,923
What, 2,000 times?

145
00:12:32,924 --> 00:12:36,760
- [Terry shouting ]
- Terry, Honey?

146
00:12:36,761 --> 00:12:38,261
Is everything okay?

147
00:12:38,262 --> 00:12:40,681
[shouting continues]

148
00:12:40,682 --> 00:12:45,682
Sorry, excuse me.

149
00:12:47,730 --> 00:12:48,772
What'd you think, Neal's back,

150
00:12:48,773 --> 00:12:50,691
you get to do whatever
the hell you want? Is that it?

151
00:12:50,692 --> 00:12:52,234
I'm sorry, Dad.

152
00:12:52,235 --> 00:12:53,235
- Dad?
- What?

153
00:12:53,236 --> 00:12:54,444
Just hold on a second.

154
00:12:54,445 --> 00:12:55,821
What do you want?
You want Neal gone?

155
00:12:55,822 --> 00:12:56,863
You want him
going back to Florida?

156
00:12:56,864 --> 00:12:58,073
- Is that it?
- Dad, come on!

157
00:12:58,074 --> 00:13:00,409
What the hell
are you thinking, Paul?

158
00:13:00,410 --> 00:13:02,911
What's going on?

159
00:13:02,912 --> 00:13:05,414
This goddamn party's over, Angela.

160
00:13:05,415 --> 00:13:07,457
I want everybody
out of my house right now.

161
00:13:07,458 --> 00:13:08,834
Everybody gone! Now!

162
00:13:08,835 --> 00:13:13,505
Okay! Okay, honey,
just listen to me, okay?

163
00:13:13,506 --> 00:13:15,674
Move your car.
You're blocking some people in.

164
00:13:15,675 --> 00:13:17,843
You have to move your car.

165
00:13:17,844 --> 00:13:22,844
Just take it easy, honey.

166
00:13:25,309 --> 00:13:29,646
Fine.

167
00:13:29,647 --> 00:13:32,190
I'm so sorry.
Are you okay?

168
00:13:32,191 --> 00:13:33,275
Yeah, I'm fine.

169
00:13:33,276 --> 00:13:35,527
How about you, Neal?

170
00:13:35,528 --> 00:13:38,113
I'm great, Angela.

171
00:13:38,114 --> 00:13:40,490
- Listen, um...
- [ money crinkling ]

172
00:13:40,491 --> 00:13:43,994
Why don't you, uh,
just take this?

173
00:13:43,995 --> 00:13:45,036
Get out of the house

174
00:13:45,037 --> 00:13:47,122
and go and be brothers
for a little bit, okay?

175
00:13:47,123 --> 00:13:52,123
Be back by 6:00
for dinner, all right?

176
00:13:58,676 --> 00:13:59,885
Thank you.

177
00:13:59,886 --> 00:14:02,596
You're welcome, honey.

178
00:14:02,597 --> 00:14:04,347
Be careful.

179
00:14:04,348 --> 00:14:07,768
Six o'clock!

180
00:14:07,769 --> 00:14:12,769
God.

181
00:14:28,748 --> 00:14:30,499
NEAL: Aah!

182
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:32,501
[Paulie laughing]

183
00:14:32,502 --> 00:14:34,669
Wow, Neal, you're here!

184
00:14:34,670 --> 00:14:36,922
That's right, dude.

185
00:14:36,923 --> 00:14:38,507
I'm here for good.

186
00:14:38,508 --> 00:14:40,175
Feels like it's been forever.

187
00:14:40,176 --> 00:14:42,177
I know, man. I can't believe
how big you got.

188
00:14:42,178 --> 00:14:46,598
I thought you were gonna be
a midget the rest of your life.

189
00:14:46,599 --> 00:14:50,811
So how was Florida
with Aunt Sara?

190
00:14:50,812 --> 00:14:53,563
Aunt Sara home-schooled me
and put me in therapy,

191
00:14:53,564 --> 00:14:57,567
so I sat around and listened
to how crazy I was for a while.

192
00:14:57,568 --> 00:15:00,529
[laughs]

193
00:15:00,530 --> 00:15:01,988
What? I miss something?

194
00:15:01,989 --> 00:15:05,784
No, it's just funny
how sometimes a crazy person

195
00:15:05,785 --> 00:15:08,537
is the only one who gets it right.

196
00:15:08,538 --> 00:15:10,914
Gets it right?

197
00:15:10,915 --> 00:15:12,582
You're not crazy, Neal.

198
00:15:12,583 --> 00:15:17,583
You never were.

199
00:15:26,681 --> 00:15:31,681
[tapping on table]

200
00:15:33,604 --> 00:15:36,106
You can smoke if you need to.

201
00:15:36,107 --> 00:15:37,524
I can't smoke in here.

202
00:15:37,525 --> 00:15:41,361
No, I just mean around me.
I don't mind.

203
00:15:41,362 --> 00:15:44,781
Thanks.

204
00:15:44,782 --> 00:15:46,408
I think I'm gonna quit.

205
00:15:46,409 --> 00:15:51,409
I have enough problems already.

206
00:15:53,374 --> 00:15:55,083
I really missed this.

207
00:15:55,084 --> 00:15:57,794
You know,
this is the coolest place in town.

208
00:15:57,795 --> 00:16:02,795
Well, what did you miss more,
this place or me?

209
00:16:03,676 --> 00:16:04,885
You jerk.

210
00:16:04,886 --> 00:16:08,430
I was just about to say you.

211
00:16:08,431 --> 00:16:11,516
Hey, guys, how's it going?

212
00:16:11,517 --> 00:16:13,602
Hi.

213
00:16:13,603 --> 00:16:18,603
Hi. Haven't seen you in forever.

214
00:16:21,569 --> 00:16:25,238
Thought my best customer
left for another diner.

215
00:16:25,239 --> 00:16:27,657
Well, um, there isn't one.

216
00:16:27,658 --> 00:16:28,700
This is the best in town.

217
00:16:28,701 --> 00:16:31,077
[ laughs ] Listen to that.

218
00:16:31,078 --> 00:16:33,246
So, you used to get the Reuben?

219
00:16:33,247 --> 00:16:36,041
- Uh-huh.
- Two, please.

220
00:16:36,042 --> 00:16:40,003
Right on it.

221
00:16:40,004 --> 00:16:42,213
So you have a girlfriend?

222
00:16:42,214 --> 00:16:44,090
No, no.

223
00:16:44,091 --> 00:16:45,300
You sure?

224
00:16:45,301 --> 00:16:48,303
I mean, there's gotta be
like ten girls after you right now.

225
00:16:48,304 --> 00:16:53,304
Well, um,
I kind of like this one girl.

226
00:16:54,268 --> 00:16:59,268
[fading and distorting ]
She sits right next to me <i>in...</i>

227
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:05,900
[ inaudible]

228
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:09,908
[ Muffled ] Neal?

229
00:17:09,909 --> 00:17:13,662
Whoa!

230
00:17:13,663 --> 00:17:14,746
Neal?

231
00:17:14,747 --> 00:17:16,081
Neal!

232
00:17:16,082 --> 00:17:20,418
[sound returns to normal ]

233
00:17:20,419 --> 00:17:25,419
Hey, let me ask you something.

234
00:17:33,724 --> 00:17:37,310
Have you seen this before?

235
00:17:37,311 --> 00:17:39,020
I don't want to talk about that.

236
00:17:39,021 --> 00:17:41,564
NEAL: It's okay.

237
00:17:41,565 --> 00:17:42,774
It's just me talking
to you, okay?

238
00:17:42,775 --> 00:17:47,775
There's nobody else but us.

239
00:17:50,992 --> 00:17:54,661
I found that sketchbook
a while back, yeah.

240
00:17:54,662 --> 00:17:57,747
I went through your boxes
a few times

241
00:17:57,748 --> 00:18:01,209
just, you know, 'cause
it made me think of you,

242
00:18:01,210 --> 00:18:04,796
- and...
- And you looked inside?

243
00:18:04,797 --> 00:18:08,883
Yeah.

244
00:18:08,884 --> 00:18:12,220
Is that what you mean
by saying that I'm not crazy?

245
00:18:12,221 --> 00:18:15,390
You think that you've been
seeing something like this?

246
00:18:15,391 --> 00:18:19,978
At night, every night.

247
00:18:19,979 --> 00:18:21,396
Who knows about this?

248
00:18:21,397 --> 00:18:22,939
You do.

249
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:25,650
Only you would ever believe
it's happening again.

250
00:18:25,651 --> 00:18:28,695
But you didn't tell Dad? Angela?

251
00:18:28,696 --> 00:18:31,781
No. Well, they know
I haven't been sleeping,

252
00:18:31,782 --> 00:18:34,534
but I don't talk about it.

253
00:18:34,535 --> 00:18:38,455
They just think it's me
missing you or school,

254
00:18:38,456 --> 00:18:43,456
and I just agree with them.

255
00:18:44,378 --> 00:18:47,380
And you think
you saw me sometimes?

256
00:18:47,381 --> 00:18:49,966
It's one of the ways
it tries to get me.

257
00:18:49,967 --> 00:18:52,802
I remembered you talking
about visions you'd have at night

258
00:18:52,803 --> 00:18:56,473
and Dad saying you've
got an overactive imagination.

259
00:18:56,474 --> 00:18:59,434
Why was all my stuff
boxed up in your room, Paulie?

260
00:18:59,435 --> 00:19:02,687
Well, when you got sent away,

261
00:19:02,688 --> 00:19:05,023
I got kind of sad,

262
00:19:05,024 --> 00:19:09,069
so Dad packed up all your stuff
and moved me in.

263
00:19:09,070 --> 00:19:10,737
He thought it would help.

264
00:19:10,738 --> 00:19:12,614
Oh, shit.

265
00:19:12,615 --> 00:19:16,451
Yeah, it didn't.

266
00:19:16,452 --> 00:19:19,204
So you've been sleeping
in my room this whole time?

267
00:19:19,205 --> 00:19:24,205
Well, I go in there every night,
but I don't sleep.

268
00:19:25,503 --> 00:19:28,630
Neal...

269
00:19:28,631 --> 00:19:33,631
you believe me, right?

270
00:19:41,727 --> 00:19:46,727
Okay.

271
00:19:48,609 --> 00:19:50,777
Ooh.

272
00:19:50,778 --> 00:19:51,861
Phew!

273
00:19:51,862 --> 00:19:55,615
Paulie, what a mess.

274
00:19:55,616 --> 00:19:58,284
See, is there anything else?

275
00:19:58,285 --> 00:20:03,285
Nope.

276
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:31,317
[rumbling]

277
00:20:31,318 --> 00:20:35,196
[ <i>Gasps</i> ]

278
00:20:35,197 --> 00:20:40,197
Damn it.

279
00:20:43,414 --> 00:20:48,414
[ slam 1

