289
00:21:25,998 --> 00:21:27,040
[quietly] Cara.

290
00:21:27,041 --> 00:21:32,041
[door bell jingles]

291
00:21:35,633 --> 00:21:38,259
What is it, Neal?

292
00:21:38,260 --> 00:21:39,469
Two Reubens!

293
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:40,720
Best in town, right, big guy?

294
00:21:40,721 --> 00:21:44,724
NEAL: [ muttering ]
Oh, my God.

295
00:21:44,725 --> 00:21:49,145
Hey, Neal.

296
00:21:49,146 --> 00:21:50,355
Wow, you've been back
for two hours

297
00:21:50,356 --> 00:21:52,106
and you're already at Melanie's.

298
00:21:52,107 --> 00:21:56,277
Heh.

299
00:21:56,278 --> 00:21:57,612
So how was your party?

300
00:21:57,613 --> 00:21:59,364
Hey, it was, <i>uh...</i>

301
00:21:59,365 --> 00:22:01,991
It was not much.

302
00:22:01,992 --> 00:22:03,910
I mean, it was fine. It was...

303
00:22:03,911 --> 00:22:08,331
Well, well, well,
if it isn't the firebug?

304
00:22:08,332 --> 00:22:09,958
You know, I heard that your dad

305
00:22:09,959 --> 00:22:11,751
had to send you away
to keep you out of jail.

306
00:22:11,752 --> 00:22:13,711
SECOND BOY: Yeah, didn't something
happen to your mom?

307
00:22:13,712 --> 00:22:18,132
Did you do that, too?

308
00:22:18,133 --> 00:22:20,885
You can't believe
everything you hear.

309
00:22:20,886 --> 00:22:23,888
He got sent away
to protect him from me.

310
00:22:23,889 --> 00:22:28,889
That's right,
I'm his brother, Paulie.

311
00:22:28,894 --> 00:22:31,145
I don't remember
what happened that night.

312
00:22:31,146 --> 00:22:33,356
When I came to
the next morning,

313
00:22:33,357 --> 00:22:35,275
he was halfway
across the country,

314
00:22:35,276 --> 00:22:38,861
and I was in a straitjacket.

315
00:22:38,862 --> 00:22:42,031
What the hell are you talking about?
You're like three.

316
00:22:42,032 --> 00:22:47,032
Mm-hmm.
That's how I get away with it.

317
00:22:48,247 --> 00:22:50,081
Let's get outta here.

318
00:22:50,082 --> 00:22:51,457
[laughs]

319
00:22:51,458 --> 00:22:53,376
You seem like you came
out of everything okay.

320
00:22:53,377 --> 00:22:58,377
Better than ever, baby.

321
00:22:58,465 --> 00:23:01,884
Wow.
So, Neal, sorry about that.

322
00:23:01,885 --> 00:23:04,137
I'll see you around, I guess.

323
00:23:04,138 --> 00:23:09,138
Yeah.

324
00:24:25,010 --> 00:24:28,262
NEAL: So...

325
00:24:28,263 --> 00:24:32,934
from the foot of the bed
or the side, most often?

326
00:24:32,935 --> 00:24:36,020
Definitely the side.

327
00:24:36,021 --> 00:24:38,523
Any idea what time?

328
00:24:38,524 --> 00:24:40,274
Not really.

329
00:24:40,275 --> 00:24:45,275
It's when it's dark and <i>late...</i>

330
00:24:45,364 --> 00:24:50,034
really late.

331
00:24:50,035 --> 00:24:52,537
Any contact?

332
00:24:52,538 --> 00:24:53,579
What do you mean?

333
00:24:53,580 --> 00:24:58,580
Like talking, messages, or...?

334
00:24:59,586 --> 00:25:03,423
I don't think so.

335
00:25:03,424 --> 00:25:06,676
What does it do?

336
00:25:06,677 --> 00:25:10,263
It reaches.

337
00:25:10,264 --> 00:25:15,264
[ Indistinct whispers ]

338
00:25:28,031 --> 00:25:30,700
Dinner, boys.

339
00:25:30,701 --> 00:25:35,701
Come on.

340
00:25:38,459 --> 00:25:39,667
TERRY:
It's very good, dear.

341
00:25:39,668 --> 00:25:41,669
ANGELA:
I see the salad is very popular.

342
00:25:41,670 --> 00:25:43,337
- It is.
- Mm-hmm.

343
00:25:43,338 --> 00:25:45,590
TERRY:
I cut mean vegetables.

344
00:25:45,591 --> 00:25:47,842
[Angela laughs]

345
00:25:47,843 --> 00:25:51,429
Oh. Isn't this wonderful?

346
00:25:51,430 --> 00:25:54,390
We're finally all here.

347
00:25:54,391 --> 00:25:57,477
So where did you
wind up going?

348
00:25:57,478 --> 00:25:58,478
[silverware clanks]

349
00:25:58,479 --> 00:26:00,021
Oh!

350
00:26:00,022 --> 00:26:01,355
ANGELA: Stop that.

351
00:26:01,356 --> 00:26:02,815
Melanie's.

352
00:26:02,816 --> 00:26:04,150
I love that place.

353
00:26:04,151 --> 00:26:06,527
It's such a great idea.

354
00:26:06,528 --> 00:26:08,154
Is that where
your appetite went, Neal?

355
00:26:08,155 --> 00:26:10,323
- Paulie? Stop that.
- Enough.

356
00:26:10,324 --> 00:26:11,657
ANGELA:
You're not tossing food.

357
00:26:11,658 --> 00:26:16,658
No, I didn't eat
my sandwich, either.

358
00:26:17,122 --> 00:26:21,792
You want me to cook
you something?

359
00:26:21,793 --> 00:26:23,377
- You sure?
- No, no.

360
00:26:23,378 --> 00:26:24,837
No, like a soufflÃ©, you know.

361
00:26:24,838 --> 00:26:25,880
[laughs]

362
00:26:25,881 --> 00:26:27,924
I'd like to see that.

363
00:26:27,925 --> 00:26:32,925
So where's Neal gonna sleep?

364
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:35,973
Well, Angela and I
talked about that a little bit,

365
00:26:35,974 --> 00:26:40,853
and, um, you know,
Paulie's in your old room,

366
00:26:40,854 --> 00:26:43,481
so we thought maybe
you'd be okay

367
00:26:43,482 --> 00:26:45,900
trying something a little different.

368
00:26:45,901 --> 00:26:47,443
I made a bed for you
in Paulie's old room.

369
00:26:47,444 --> 00:26:49,570
I hope that's okay.

370
00:26:49,571 --> 00:26:51,280
Paulie's room.

371
00:26:51,281 --> 00:26:53,950
That's great, considering that all--

372
00:26:53,951 --> 00:26:58,951
all my shit is in there.

373
00:27:48,755 --> 00:27:53,755
[school bell rings]

374
00:28:40,599 --> 00:28:44,268
So nice to see
many of your happy faces here

375
00:28:44,269 --> 00:28:46,604
supporting theater in the schools.

376
00:28:46,605 --> 00:28:50,066
Maybe that'll send
the school board a message, huh?

377
00:28:50,067 --> 00:28:52,818
Well, you might have noticed
that our turnout

378
00:28:52,819 --> 00:28:56,989
for this year's school play
is a little light.

379
00:28:56,990 --> 00:28:58,866
You can thank your parents
for responding so well

380
00:28:58,867 --> 00:29:01,243
to my original piece I wrote,

381
00:29:01,244 --> 00:29:06,244
"Barry Bonds:
Hero or Cheater?"

382
00:29:16,635 --> 00:29:19,387
Undaunted, I'm gonna move on
to my next project,

383
00:29:19,388 --> 00:29:21,097
which will be a lot of fun.

384
00:29:21,098 --> 00:29:24,141
We're gonna do "The Crucible,
the Musical," and...

385
00:29:24,142 --> 00:29:28,813
[ music]

386
00:29:28,814 --> 00:29:33,814
[dialogue inaudible]

387
00:30:03,682 --> 00:30:08,682
[ Spotlight clicks ]

388
00:30:23,994 --> 00:30:25,286
Wake up!

389
00:30:25,287 --> 00:30:27,621
Aah! [echoing ]

390
00:30:27,622 --> 00:30:29,915
Aah!

391
00:30:29,916 --> 00:30:34,916
Aah!

392
00:31:05,035 --> 00:31:09,872
Look, I get that you need
some time to readjust, Neal.

393
00:31:09,873 --> 00:31:11,916
Okay, I do,

394
00:31:11,917 --> 00:31:14,585
but I got you two
staring off into nothing.

395
00:31:14,586 --> 00:31:15,753
You're not eating.

396
00:31:15,754 --> 00:31:18,631
You sure as shit don't care
about Angela's feelings.

397
00:31:18,632 --> 00:31:21,300
And you know what
I don't want, boys?

398
00:31:21,301 --> 00:31:26,301
I don't want today
to become every other day.

399
00:31:26,556 --> 00:31:29,225
We used to be normal.

400
00:31:29,226 --> 00:31:32,061
Do you remember that?

401
00:31:32,062 --> 00:31:34,563
We're gonna be again.

402
00:31:34,564 --> 00:31:39,564
We're gonna be,
but it's up to you boys.

403
00:31:41,071 --> 00:31:44,448
Paulie?

404
00:31:44,449 --> 00:31:45,533
Angela and I have decided

405
00:31:45,534 --> 00:31:47,243
we're gonna keep you
out of school for a little while.

406
00:31:47,244 --> 00:31:49,620
No. No, no, no,
you can't do that!

407
00:31:49,621 --> 00:31:50,955
Why?

408
00:31:50,956 --> 00:31:54,667
Why?
Are you actually asking why?

409
00:31:54,668 --> 00:31:56,418
Should we ask
all your--your classmates

410
00:31:56,419 --> 00:32:00,548
who watched you
melt down today why, Paulie?

411
00:32:00,549 --> 00:32:03,801
Now, look, the--the priority
here is to get you guys

412
00:32:03,802 --> 00:32:06,762
both back to earth
and back in school in a week,

413
00:32:06,763 --> 00:32:10,558
and we are gonna do it!

414
00:32:10,559 --> 00:32:13,352
But before I can enroll you, Neal,

415
00:32:13,353 --> 00:32:15,145
I need you to do
some things for me, son.

416
00:32:15,146 --> 00:32:17,189
Oh, yeah? What's that?

417
00:32:17,190 --> 00:32:22,190
Like grow the fuck up, for one.

418
00:32:22,445 --> 00:32:26,365
Like become a man!

419
00:32:26,366 --> 00:32:27,783
You're were only supposed
to go down to Sara's

420
00:32:27,784 --> 00:32:29,869
for a couple of months,

421
00:32:29,870 --> 00:32:32,121
but she wanted you there
because she thought it was helping.

422
00:32:32,122 --> 00:32:34,164
But if two years down there
is not getting you to grow up,

423
00:32:34,165 --> 00:32:35,416
then I'm gonna do it!

424
00:32:35,417 --> 00:32:37,668
Your ass is getting a job!

425
00:32:37,669 --> 00:32:39,795
Is getting a job
gonna make me a man?

426
00:32:39,796 --> 00:32:41,964
Well, it's sure as shit gonna help!

427
00:32:41,965 --> 00:32:46,010
Uh, Neal, honey?
I think what your dad

428
00:32:46,011 --> 00:32:47,553
is trying to say is that

429
00:32:47,554 --> 00:32:51,348
[fading and distorting ]
Paulie needs a role model.

430
00:32:51,349 --> 00:32:53,100
[voice becomes indistinct]

431
00:32:53,101 --> 00:32:54,602
[ Indistinct whispering ]

432
00:32:54,603 --> 00:32:57,021
ANGELA: [ muffled ]
Are you okay?

433
00:32:57,022 --> 00:32:59,148
[door bangs]

434
00:32:59,149 --> 00:33:00,816
- Neal! Are you listening?
- Yes!

435
00:33:00,817 --> 00:33:02,443
Yes? Okay, then
what did we just say?

436
00:33:02,444 --> 00:33:03,736
That I'm still crazy!

437
00:33:03,737 --> 00:33:05,154
No, that is not
what we just said!

438
00:33:05,155 --> 00:33:06,655
That's all that anybody thinks!

439
00:33:06,656 --> 00:33:08,407
I'm not even getting a chance!

440
00:33:08,408 --> 00:33:09,700
You don't get chances, kid!

441
00:33:09,701 --> 00:33:11,410
You earn them,
and you're not doing it!

442
00:33:11,411 --> 00:33:16,411
Well, maybe I should have
just died with Mom!

443
00:33:21,504 --> 00:33:26,504
You two go to bed.

444
00:33:33,141 --> 00:33:34,224
Angela's making
you act completely...

445
00:33:34,225 --> 00:33:36,518
TERRY: Stop it, Neal.

446
00:33:36,519 --> 00:33:39,605
Please just stop talking,
all right?

447
00:33:39,606 --> 00:33:42,024
Now, you two brought
this on yourselves.

448
00:33:42,025 --> 00:33:44,193
This door's gonna stay locked.

449
00:33:44,194 --> 00:33:45,986
You gotta go to the bathroom,
you knock.

450
00:33:45,987 --> 00:33:50,987
Otherwise,
all I want to hear is silence.

451
00:33:52,577 --> 00:33:57,577
Sleep tight!

452
00:34:01,962 --> 00:34:03,337
Don't start with me.

453
00:34:03,338 --> 00:34:04,964
Maybe we should consider
outside help.

454
00:34:04,965 --> 00:34:07,299
No. We've done that,
and it hasn't done jack shit.

455
00:34:07,300 --> 00:34:08,801
We are doing this ourselves.

456
00:34:08,802 --> 00:34:10,928
But something
is going on here, Terry.

457
00:34:10,929 --> 00:34:12,680
Yes, Angela, there is,

458
00:34:12,681 --> 00:34:17,681
and we're gonna put a stop to it.

459
00:34:19,771 --> 00:34:22,231
NEAL:
You sleep with the light on?

460
00:34:22,232 --> 00:34:25,275
PAULIE: At night, yeah.

461
00:34:25,276 --> 00:34:27,361
NEAL: For how long?

462
00:34:27,362 --> 00:34:32,324
PAULIE: About a year now.

463
00:34:32,325 --> 00:34:35,160
NEAL: But it helps?

464
00:34:35,161 --> 00:34:40,161
PAULIE: Mm-mmm.

465
00:34:51,845 --> 00:34:56,845
[ Floor creaks ]

466
00:34:57,267 --> 00:35:00,644
Hey, let's try something,

467
00:35:00,645 --> 00:35:05,441
you and me.

468
00:35:05,442 --> 00:35:10,442
Turn the light off.

469
00:35:16,119 --> 00:35:21,119
Neal, what are you gonna do?

470
00:35:22,751 --> 00:35:27,751
[whispers ] Hey.

471
00:35:32,052 --> 00:35:33,761
[ Soft snarl ]

472
00:35:33,762 --> 00:35:34,803
Hey!

473
00:35:34,804 --> 00:35:39,804
[ Loud roar]

474
00:35:42,103 --> 00:35:44,772
If we don't make any noise,

475
00:35:44,773 --> 00:35:49,568
it doesn't know we're here.

476
00:35:49,569 --> 00:35:54,364
What about when we move?

477
00:35:54,365 --> 00:35:59,365
Here, let me try something.

478
00:36:01,039 --> 00:36:02,664
[floor creaking ]

479
00:36:02,665 --> 00:36:07,665
[ Monster snarling ]

480
00:36:14,427 --> 00:36:17,554
So we don't move,
we don't make any sound,

481
00:36:17,555 --> 00:36:19,515
it's not gonna try anything, right?

482
00:36:19,516 --> 00:36:24,516
- [ Roaring ]
- Paulie, he's right behind you, man!

483
00:36:27,315 --> 00:36:31,777
[ Roar echoes and fades ]

484
00:36:31,778 --> 00:36:36,778
[Sighs]

485
00:36:39,285 --> 00:36:41,078
How close did it come to me?

486
00:36:41,079 --> 00:36:43,705
Um, not that close.

487
00:36:43,706 --> 00:36:46,125
Still had half the room to go.

488
00:36:46,126 --> 00:36:49,253
A couple of feet.

489
00:36:49,254 --> 00:36:52,256
We're all right
with the lights on, I think.

490
00:36:52,257 --> 00:36:55,509
Yeah.

491
00:36:55,510 --> 00:37:00,055
Wonder what Angela tells Dad.

492
00:37:00,056 --> 00:37:02,057
What do you think of her?

493
00:37:02,058 --> 00:37:04,643
She's kind of cool.

494
00:37:04,644 --> 00:37:07,104
Seriously?

495
00:37:07,105 --> 00:37:09,606
Does she even have a job?

496
00:37:09,607 --> 00:37:12,151
She's a substitute teacher.

497
00:37:12,152 --> 00:37:14,319
Good for her.

498
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:17,114
Substitute teacher,
substitute wife,

499
00:37:17,115 --> 00:37:20,576
substitute mom.

500
00:37:20,577 --> 00:37:24,079
She's got it all figured out.

501
00:37:24,080 --> 00:37:29,080
Neal, you should give her a chance.

502
00:37:29,127 --> 00:37:34,127
Does Dad ever talk about Mom?

503
00:37:34,257 --> 00:37:39,257
Never, except
when he'd talk about you.

504
00:37:40,680 --> 00:37:43,891
Does he blame me?

505
00:37:43,892 --> 00:37:46,935
He blames everybody.

506
00:37:46,936 --> 00:37:49,396
<i>'</i> Hey, Neal?
'Hmm?

507
00:37:49,397 --> 00:37:51,732
Want to see how I get to bed?

508
00:37:51,733 --> 00:37:56,733
Yeah.

509
00:38:20,470 --> 00:38:25,432
[ Loud roar]

510
00:38:25,433 --> 00:38:29,269
[ Roar fades ]

511
00:38:29,270 --> 00:38:30,771
So I was thinking
about how we'd keep you

512
00:38:30,772 --> 00:38:32,564
off the floor tonight, Neal.

513
00:38:32,565 --> 00:38:36,276
I was just gonna
stay up all night.

514
00:38:36,277 --> 00:38:38,987
Not like I haven't done it before.

515
00:38:38,988 --> 00:38:41,657
Well, maybe you can
sleep on the dresser.

516
00:38:41,658 --> 00:38:46,658
I mean, better than no sleep.

517
00:38:47,205 --> 00:38:52,205
Worth a shot.

518
00:38:52,210 --> 00:38:57,210
Just run, Neal.
You're gonna make it mad.

519
00:39:00,009 --> 00:39:05,009
[ Loud roar]

520
00:39:08,434 --> 00:39:12,604
[ Roaring ]

521
00:39:12,605 --> 00:39:14,690
I think I made it mad anyway.

522
00:39:14,691 --> 00:39:19,691
Well, it's a lot noisier
than it's ever been before.

523
00:39:21,489 --> 00:39:25,158
It remembers me.

524
00:39:25,159 --> 00:39:28,078
It's been a long two years, Neal.

525
00:39:28,079 --> 00:39:31,999
I'm glad you haven't changed.

526
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:35,294
What happened to you today?

527
00:39:35,295 --> 00:39:40,295
I fell asleep in class,
and I woke up screaming.

528
00:39:40,883 --> 00:39:44,344
Why didn't you
say anything, man?

529
00:39:44,345 --> 00:39:48,849
Well, 'cause I kind of
like just hanging out

530
00:39:48,850 --> 00:39:53,850
without talking about screaming.

531
00:39:56,941 --> 00:40:01,862
You ready to stop screaming?

532
00:40:01,863 --> 00:40:06,491
Yeah.

533
00:40:06,492 --> 00:40:11,492
[Sighs]

534
00:40:35,772 --> 00:40:40,772
[ Indistinct whispers ]

535
00:40:57,335 --> 00:41:02,335
[object banging and rattling ]

536
00:41:02,715 --> 00:41:03,965
Paulie?

537
00:41:03,966 --> 00:41:06,301
Paulie! Paulie,
if you're sleeping, wake up!

538
00:41:06,302 --> 00:41:08,178
Wake up, man,
there's something happening!

539
00:41:08,179 --> 00:41:10,764
PAULIE: Yeah, this stuff.

540
00:41:10,765 --> 00:41:11,973
I don't remember this!

541
00:41:11,974 --> 00:41:13,642
What the fuck is this, man?

542
00:41:13,643 --> 00:41:15,811
Usually happens
after I've already fallen asleep.

543
00:41:15,812 --> 00:41:20,812
[ Bangs and crashes]

544
00:41:26,364 --> 00:41:27,656
What's happening?!

545
00:41:27,657 --> 00:41:29,825
I don't know, Paulie!
Hang on!

546
00:41:29,826 --> 00:41:34,826
[clattering ]

547
00:41:35,498 --> 00:41:40,498
[ Noise stops]

548
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:45,920
[ Indistinct whispers ]

549
00:42:07,780 --> 00:42:09,156
[Crash ]

550
00:42:09,157 --> 00:42:12,409
[objects clatter]

551
00:42:12,410 --> 00:42:14,744
Dad!

552
00:42:14,745 --> 00:42:15,704
NEAL:
Dad, what are you doing?

553
00:42:15,705 --> 00:42:17,247
Dad, leave him alone!

554
00:42:17,248 --> 00:42:19,040
Dad! Dad!
What are you doing?

555
00:42:19,041 --> 00:42:20,625
[ Paulie groans]

556
00:42:20,626 --> 00:42:22,210
- NEAL: Get off him, Dad!
- PAULIE: Dad, what--

557
00:42:22,211 --> 00:42:23,211
- NEAL: Stop!
- Dad!

558
00:42:23,212 --> 00:42:25,755
- [ Monster Terry growling ]
- PAULIE: Neal!

559
00:42:25,756 --> 00:42:27,215
No! Dad!

560
00:42:27,216 --> 00:42:28,884
Dad, stop!

561
00:42:28,885 --> 00:42:31,052
NEAL: Dad! Dad!

562
00:42:31,053 --> 00:42:33,388
- [ Hissing and snarling ]
- PAULIE: No, no!

563
00:42:33,389 --> 00:42:35,348
[growling]

564
00:42:35,349 --> 00:42:40,349
Aah!

565
00:42:46,027 --> 00:42:48,487
[wincing ]

566
00:42:48,488 --> 00:42:49,738
ANGELA: Does it hurt?

567
00:42:49,739 --> 00:42:53,200
PAULIE: Mm-hmm.

568
00:42:53,201 --> 00:42:56,745
Do you want to tell me
exactly what happened, honey?

569
00:42:56,746 --> 00:43:00,248
No.

570
00:43:00,249 --> 00:43:02,501
Paulie, you know,
I can put medicine on your bruises

571
00:43:02,502 --> 00:43:04,628
in the middle of the night,

572
00:43:04,629 --> 00:43:06,254
but the only way
I can truly help you

573
00:43:06,255 --> 00:43:11,255
is if I can stop this
from happening in the first place.

574
00:43:15,681 --> 00:43:19,976
Paulie, honey, I love you,

575
00:43:19,977 --> 00:43:24,564
and I really want to help you,
but you have to trust me.

576
00:43:24,565 --> 00:43:27,150
Please trust me.

577
00:43:27,151 --> 00:43:29,819
Okay, you have two ways
of answering this for me.

578
00:43:29,820 --> 00:43:32,072
Either you did this,
or he did this to himself.

579
00:43:32,073 --> 00:43:34,658
- Which one is it?
- No.

580
00:43:34,659 --> 00:43:36,618
Which answer, Neal?

581
00:43:36,619 --> 00:43:38,495
Which answer is gonna
make <i>us less</i> miserable?

582
00:43:38,496 --> 00:43:39,538
You don't really think

583
00:43:39,539 --> 00:43:43,416
that I would ever
do that to him, do you?

584
00:43:43,417 --> 00:43:44,459
So he did it to himself?

585
00:43:44,460 --> 00:43:46,002
I didn't say that.

586
00:43:46,003 --> 00:43:47,045
God damn it, Neal!

587
00:43:47,046 --> 00:43:49,506
Knock this shit off, please!

588
00:43:49,507 --> 00:43:51,591
'Cause I don't think
you two can survive another day!

589
00:43:51,592 --> 00:43:55,720
I don't think I can survive
another day of this!

590
00:43:55,721 --> 00:43:59,266
I know.

591
00:43:59,267 --> 00:44:02,978
This is not the way to protect
your little brother.

592
00:44:02,979 --> 00:44:05,855
You know, he doesn't need you
making excuses for him.

593
00:44:05,856 --> 00:44:09,943
He needs you being a man,
standing up for him.

594
00:44:09,944 --> 00:44:14,944
I'm trying.

595
00:44:17,368 --> 00:44:19,494
Dad thinks you did it.

596
00:44:19,495 --> 00:44:21,413
Really?

597
00:44:21,414 --> 00:44:23,248
Angela thinks you did it.

598
00:44:23,249 --> 00:44:28,249
She does?

599
00:44:28,754 --> 00:44:32,882
If she says that to my face,
I'm gonna call her a bitch to hers.

600
00:44:32,883 --> 00:44:37,883
Well, then that'd be
the first time you talked to her.

601
00:44:40,933 --> 00:44:44,185
Did it hurt when it grabbed you?

602
00:44:44,186 --> 00:44:45,895
<i>No, it...</i>

603
00:44:45,896 --> 00:44:47,897
It felt worse.

604
00:44:47,898 --> 00:44:50,191
Like what'd it feel like?

605
00:44:50,192 --> 00:44:52,611
It was cold and...
and numb,

606
00:44:52,612 --> 00:44:54,487
and it felt like I was...

607
00:44:54,488 --> 00:44:57,866
Falling asleep?

608
00:44:57,867 --> 00:44:59,618
Yeah.

609
00:44:59,619 --> 00:45:03,955
Jesus Christ.

610
00:45:03,956 --> 00:45:06,291
Okay, boys, it's late.

611
00:45:06,292 --> 00:45:11,292
Let's try this again, shall we?

612
00:45:14,175 --> 00:45:18,386
ANGELA: Come on, honey,
let's get you back to bed.

613
00:45:18,387 --> 00:45:20,597
Honey, come here.

614
00:45:20,598 --> 00:45:22,599
I'm really worried about you.

615
00:45:22,600 --> 00:45:24,643
How can I make this better?

616
00:45:24,644 --> 00:45:26,144
PAULIE:
Can I have my sleeping bag?

617
00:45:26,145 --> 00:45:27,103
ANGELA:
Sure, I'll go get your sleeping...

618
00:45:27,104 --> 00:45:29,481
TERRY:
No. Paulie's sleeping in a bed

619
00:45:29,482 --> 00:45:31,149
like a normal person,

620
00:45:31,150 --> 00:45:35,528
and this door is staying locked.

621
00:45:35,529 --> 00:45:37,322
The sooner you two
get past this phase...

622
00:45:37,323 --> 00:45:38,657
[ unscrewing light bulb]

623
00:45:38,658 --> 00:45:40,200
The sooner we can
go on living our lives.

624
00:45:40,201 --> 00:45:41,201
ANGELA:
What are you doing?

625
00:45:41,202 --> 00:45:42,452
TERRY:
What am I doing?

626
00:45:42,453 --> 00:45:44,537
Normal people sleep in the dark!

627
00:45:44,538 --> 00:45:45,664
So is he!

628
00:45:45,665 --> 00:45:46,956
ANGELA:
It's a little extreme, Terry.

629
00:45:46,957 --> 00:45:51,957
TERRY: Come on, please?
Come on.

630
00:46:27,623 --> 00:46:32,623
[ Lock clicking ]

631
00:46:37,425 --> 00:46:42,425
PAULIE: Neal.

632
00:46:45,307 --> 00:46:50,307
NEAL: Come on.

633
00:47:44,325 --> 00:47:47,452
TERRY: Boys?

634
00:47:47,453 --> 00:47:51,456
Paulie? Neal?

635
00:47:51,457 --> 00:47:54,793
Wake up.

636
00:47:54,794 --> 00:47:58,171
Good morning.

637
00:47:58,172 --> 00:48:00,173
You okay?

638
00:48:00,174 --> 00:48:05,174
NEAL:
Yeah, Dad, we're both fine.

639
00:48:05,513 --> 00:48:06,721
TERRY: Okay, Well, <i>it's...</i>

640
00:48:06,722 --> 00:48:09,682
It's breakfast time.

641
00:48:09,683 --> 00:48:14,683
Come on.

642
00:48:15,439 --> 00:48:16,606
I know. Thank you, Sam.

643
00:48:16,607 --> 00:48:18,733
I really appreciate it.

644
00:48:18,734 --> 00:48:20,276
Yes, I will.

645
00:48:20,277 --> 00:48:25,277
Thanks. Bye-bye.

646
00:48:26,784 --> 00:48:28,243
They understand.

647
00:48:28,244 --> 00:48:31,746
They're not happy,
but they...they get it.

648
00:48:31,747 --> 00:48:33,540
I'm sorry, Ang.

649
00:48:33,541 --> 00:48:38,294
It's okay, honey.
It's not your fault.

650
00:48:38,295 --> 00:48:40,588
[Sighs]

651
00:48:40,589 --> 00:48:44,133
I found Neal in Paulie's room
this morning.

652
00:48:44,134 --> 00:48:46,344
- What?
- Snuck in.

653
00:48:46,345 --> 00:48:48,221
Oh, my gosh.

654
00:48:48,222 --> 00:48:50,932
At least they didn't
kill each other.

655
00:48:50,933 --> 00:48:54,853
Oh, honey, I'm so sorry.

656
00:48:54,854 --> 00:48:59,854
I swear to God, Ang,
I have no idea what to do.

657
00:49:03,362 --> 00:49:06,781
Did Dad tell you
about Mom's grave?

658
00:49:06,782 --> 00:49:10,869
One of his letters
had pictures of it.

659
00:49:10,870 --> 00:49:15,870
Yeah, well, she's not there.

660
00:49:20,963 --> 00:49:25,963
No fuckin' way.

661
00:49:26,135 --> 00:49:28,219
I wanted her to stay here,

662
00:49:28,220 --> 00:49:33,099
and Dad said it was okay
as long as he didn't see it.

663
00:49:33,100 --> 00:49:38,100
So I keep it in here.

664
00:49:48,782 --> 00:49:53,782
[ Sniffles ]

665
00:50:05,424 --> 00:50:09,427
You remember Mom
staying in the house

666
00:50:09,428 --> 00:50:14,182
after the fire reached
the living room?

667
00:50:14,183 --> 00:50:17,852
That night...

668
00:50:17,853 --> 00:50:19,228
I begged her to stay with me

669
00:50:19,229 --> 00:50:21,731
so she could see
what was under the bed.

670
00:50:21,732 --> 00:50:26,653
She did, and...

671
00:50:26,654 --> 00:50:31,654
she died because she believed me.

672
00:50:32,117 --> 00:50:37,117
She was protecting us.

673
00:50:39,416 --> 00:50:41,834
I miss her.

674
00:50:41,835 --> 00:50:46,835
[ Car door closes,
engine starts ]

675
00:51:09,655 --> 00:51:14,158
Look, you gotta hold it
from the side, too.

676
00:51:14,159 --> 00:51:15,702
Keep your finger
on the trigger.

677
00:51:15,703 --> 00:51:17,620
Keep it steady and push forward
with your back hand.

678
00:51:17,621 --> 00:51:20,665
In.

679
00:51:20,666 --> 00:51:23,084
You'd have to be pretty close
to hurt it with this, right?

680
00:51:23,085 --> 00:51:26,004
Well, yeah.

681
00:51:26,005 --> 00:51:27,130
We'd have to get closer

682
00:51:27,131 --> 00:51:32,131
than we've ever been
before sooner or later.

683
00:51:39,393 --> 00:51:44,063
[clattering ]

684
00:51:44,064 --> 00:51:49,064
What makes you think
we can kill it?

685
00:51:49,236 --> 00:51:52,196
I think it's afraid of us,

686
00:51:52,197 --> 00:51:55,533
and it wouldn't be afraid of anything
if it couldn't die, Paul.

687
00:51:55,534 --> 00:52:00,534
Would you be?

688
00:52:02,708 --> 00:52:07,378
We're something this thing
has never dealt with before.

689
00:52:07,379 --> 00:52:12,379
What?

690
00:52:16,722 --> 00:52:21,392
We're brothers.

691
00:52:21,393 --> 00:52:24,479
Oh, shit.

692
00:52:24,480 --> 00:52:25,855
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

693
00:52:25,856 --> 00:52:28,649
Uh, Neal, dear?

694
00:52:28,650 --> 00:52:31,277
Let's leave that alone
for the time being.

695
00:52:31,278 --> 00:52:33,529
Dad taught me to use it before.

696
00:52:33,530 --> 00:52:36,824
Well, he's not here
right now, so, uh,

697
00:52:36,825 --> 00:52:37,909
put it down.

698
00:52:37,910 --> 00:52:39,202
I'll be fine.

699
00:52:39,203 --> 00:52:41,996
Put it down,

700
00:52:41,997 --> 00:52:46,250
please.

701
00:52:46,251 --> 00:52:50,088
[ Chainsaw thuds ]

702
00:52:50,089 --> 00:52:55,089
Come on, pal.

703
00:52:57,930 --> 00:52:59,013
Paulie?

704
00:52:59,014 --> 00:53:01,182
Sweetheart,

705
00:53:01,183 --> 00:53:02,892
please tell me what's going on.

706
00:53:02,893 --> 00:53:04,352
It's not a big deal.

707
00:53:04,353 --> 00:53:06,104
Well, if you can just tell me
a little bit, honey,

708
00:53:06,105 --> 00:53:10,858
maybe I can, I don't know,
somehow help you?

709
00:53:10,859 --> 00:53:15,859
If you want to help him,
stay out of his way.

710
00:54:02,744 --> 00:54:04,579
NEAL:
It looks pretty good in there.

711
00:54:04,580 --> 00:54:09,580
PAULIE: Yeah, not bad for two hours
of sleep between us.

712
00:54:27,227 --> 00:54:30,313
We're okay.

713
00:54:30,314 --> 00:54:34,317
Before I got sent away,
I used to sleep anywhere I could,

714
00:54:34,318 --> 00:54:36,694
like the kitchen,
Mom and Dad's room, outside.

715
00:54:36,695 --> 00:54:38,070
I slept in the garage
a few times,

716
00:54:38,071 --> 00:54:40,698
but it only ever got to me

717
00:54:40,699 --> 00:54:43,201
when I would
try to sleep in beds.

718
00:54:43,202 --> 00:54:46,954
It's bound to beds.

719
00:54:46,955 --> 00:54:48,414
Why?

720
00:54:48,415 --> 00:54:51,500
I don't know.

721
00:54:51,501 --> 00:54:53,544
I have theories, I guess.

722
00:54:53,545 --> 00:54:56,464
Beds are where people
sleep the most,

723
00:54:56,465 --> 00:54:58,257
so if it usually strikes
when you sleep,

724
00:54:58,258 --> 00:55:00,176
it makes sense.

725
00:55:00,177 --> 00:55:02,178
That's where you have
the most dreams

726
00:55:02,179 --> 00:55:04,305
and nightmares.

727
00:55:04,306 --> 00:55:06,599
Maybe that's what it looks for.

728
00:55:06,600 --> 00:55:10,186
Maybe.

729
00:55:10,187 --> 00:55:12,813
I have another theory, too,

730
00:55:12,814 --> 00:55:15,900
but you can't freak out.

731
00:55:15,901 --> 00:55:20,071
Go ahead.

732
00:55:20,072 --> 00:55:21,906
I read once that you shed

733
00:55:21,907 --> 00:55:24,492
a lot of dead skin cells
in your bed.

734
00:55:24,493 --> 00:55:26,786
Like while you sleep,
you know, like,

735
00:55:26,787 --> 00:55:29,830
your bed is full of dead skin

736
00:55:29,831 --> 00:55:34,210
and pieces of your body.

737
00:55:34,211 --> 00:55:37,380
Maybe it starts
by, like, feeding on--

738
00:55:37,381 --> 00:55:39,715
on your dead flesh
before it, you know...

739
00:55:39,716 --> 00:55:43,010
PAULIE: Before that's
not good enough anymore.

740
00:55:43,011 --> 00:55:48,011
NEAL: Yeah.

741
00:55:55,524 --> 00:56:00,524
PAULIE:
You looking at that old Polaroid?

742
00:56:00,779 --> 00:56:04,282
Yeah. You know about this?

743
00:56:04,283 --> 00:56:08,286
Yeah, I found it after you left.

744
00:56:08,287 --> 00:56:11,038
PAULIE:
So that's what it looks like, right?

745
00:56:11,039 --> 00:56:13,916
That crazy face?

746
00:56:13,917 --> 00:56:17,044
I guess.

747
00:56:17,045 --> 00:56:22,008
I never tried to take
another picture after this one, so...

748
00:56:22,009 --> 00:56:26,220
I did.

749
00:56:26,221 --> 00:56:28,222
You did?

750
00:56:28,223 --> 00:56:30,308
Yeah.

751
00:56:30,309 --> 00:56:32,643
I thought that
if I could prove it was real

752
00:56:32,644 --> 00:56:37,106
then you'd come back
sooner, you know.

753
00:56:37,107 --> 00:56:39,692
So I started taking
pictures under the bed,

754
00:56:39,693 --> 00:56:41,777
staying up late, making noise,

755
00:56:41,778 --> 00:56:43,738
you know, stuff like that.

756
00:56:43,739 --> 00:56:48,739
Until one night,
that mist came out of nowhere,

757
00:56:48,785 --> 00:56:53,785
and it's never gone
away since then.

758
00:56:56,877 --> 00:57:01,877
NEAL: Can you sleep?

759
00:57:08,347 --> 00:57:13,347
[Sighs]

760
00:57:42,672 --> 00:57:47,672
[ Indistinct whispers ]

761
00:57:53,350 --> 00:57:56,560
Neal? Neal!

762
00:57:56,561 --> 00:58:01,561
NEAL: What?

763
00:58:04,861 --> 00:58:08,155
[scraping ]

764
00:58:08,156 --> 00:58:10,616
[thud]

765
00:58:10,617 --> 00:58:12,827
Run.

766
00:58:12,828 --> 00:58:14,412
Come on, Paulie, this way!

767
00:58:14,413 --> 00:58:16,872
[Crash ]

768
00:58:16,873 --> 00:58:18,165
[ Both panting ]

769
00:58:18,166 --> 00:58:20,292
- [Crash]
<i>'</i> Oh, my God!

770
00:58:20,293 --> 00:58:23,963
[ Rattling ]

771
00:58:23,964 --> 00:58:28,964
[ Monster growling ]

772
00:58:30,595 --> 00:58:32,054
[ Roaring ]

773
00:58:32,055 --> 00:58:34,348
Paulie, that's my old bed!

774
00:58:34,349 --> 00:58:35,641
[ Hissing and roaring ]

775
00:58:35,642 --> 00:58:40,642
[loud thuds]

776
00:58:41,815 --> 00:58:43,399
NEAL: Aah!

777
00:58:43,400 --> 00:58:48,112
[ Both screaming ]

778
00:58:48,113 --> 00:58:53,113
[ Noise stops]

779
00:59:01,793 --> 00:59:04,086
NEAL: You okay?

780
00:59:04,087 --> 00:59:09,087
PAULIE: No.

781
00:59:22,397 --> 00:59:24,398
TERRY:
Come on, boys, wake up.

782
00:59:24,399 --> 00:59:29,399
You been asleep all afternoon.

783
00:59:33,116 --> 00:59:35,493
What is all that?

784
00:59:35,494 --> 00:59:37,578
We're gonna try
something new tonight,

785
00:59:37,579 --> 00:59:39,830
something fun.

786
00:59:39,831 --> 00:59:41,916
Mr. Evans next door
has offered

787
00:59:41,917 --> 00:59:43,751
to have you guys
spend the night.

788
00:59:43,752 --> 00:59:47,379
His boys would love to have
you both for a sleepover.

789
00:59:47,380 --> 00:59:50,382
[scoffs] You gotta be
fucking joking.

790
00:59:50,383 --> 00:59:52,426
TERRY: Neal, come on.

791
00:59:52,427 --> 00:59:54,386
Dad, didn't you just finish telling us
we need to grow up?

792
00:59:54,387 --> 00:59:55,554
I mean, what the hell?

793
00:59:55,555 --> 00:59:57,556
- Neal, stop it.
- They're expecting you anytime,

794
00:59:57,557 --> 00:59:59,141
so whenever you're ready,
up you come, boys.

795
00:59:59,142 --> 01:00:01,769
Come on, it's gonna be fun.

796
01:00:01,770 --> 01:00:03,103
Paulie, you're
